oserver
-------

dev installation
----------------

http://pinaxproject.com/docs/dev/contributing.html

(Note: For Max OSX use the full path to the python, it has troubles with symbolic links)

** setup virtual env: **
pc> python lib/pinax/scripts/pinax-boot.py --development --source=lib/pinax pinax-dev
mac>/System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.6/bin/python2.6 lib/pinax/scripts/pinax-boot.py --development --source=lib/pinax pinax-dev

** activate virtual env: **
mac> source pinax-dev/bin/activate
pc> pinax-dev\Scripts\activate.bat

TODO: remove this line, freeze requirements and store them locally in our requirements.txt
** install external requirements: **
> pip install --no-deps --requirement lib/pinax/requirements/external_apps.txt

# TODO: create githook for this automatically
** update 'local' requirements: (done after each sync) **
> pip install --no-deps -r requirements.txt

> python manage.py syncdb --noinput
> python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000



** to send emails: **
> python manage.py send_mail


** when pinax/lib changes **
> git submodule update
> pip install --no-deps --requirement lib/pinax/requirements/external_apps.txt
> pip install --no-deps -r requirements.txt

